'' Mainstream Top 40]]<ref name=\"allmusic\"/>\n|align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n|US [[Rhythmic Airplay Chart|''Billboard'' Rhythmic Top 40]]<ref name=\"allmusic\"/>\n|align=\"center\"|15\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n{{Sean Combs}}\n{{Black Rob}}\n\n[[Category:2001 singles]]\n[[Category:2001 songs]]\n[[Category:Sean Combs songs]]\n[[Category:Bad Boy Records singles]]\n[[Category:Music videos directed by Chris Robinson (director)]]\n", "name_user": "Alexandrktl", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u041f\u0435\u0441\u043d\u044f \u0442\u0430\u043a-\u0436\u0435 \u0438\u0441\u043f\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0437\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0430\u0441\u044c \u0432 \u0444\u0438\u043b\u044c\u043c\u0435 \"\u041a\u0440\u0435\u043f\u0438\u0441\u044c\" (Get Hard) - \u0418\u0442\u0430\u043d \u041a\u043e\u044d\u043d.  2015", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bad_Boy_for_Life"}
{"title_page": "Angel Air Records", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2015}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2015}}\n{{Refimprove|date=September 2014}}\n{{Infobox record label <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Music -->\n| name        = Angel Air\n| image       = Angel_air_records_logo.gif\n| founded     = {{start date|1997}}\n| founder     = Peter Purnell, Shirley Purnell\n| distributor = Proper Music (UK)\n| genre       = Pop, rock, progressive rock, folk, world music, dance\n| country     = England\n| location    = Stowmarket, Suffolk\n| website      = {{URL|www.angelair.co.uk}}\n}}\n'''Angel Air''' is an English [[independent record label]] established in February 1997, specialising in reissues of classic [[pop music|pop]] and [[rock music|rock]] albums originally issued in the 1960s and 1970s (and latterly new albums from known artists up to the 21st century). It was formed by Peter and Shirley Purnell.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.angelair.co.uk/book_catalogue.htm |title=Angel Air Records - Classic Rock and Pop CD Albums - reissues, collectors items and new recordings |publisher=Angelair.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2013-03-02}}</ref> \n\nToday the Purnells also own CeeDee Music UK which publishes over 3,000 songs, and CeeDee Management which counts [[Mott The Hoople]] members the late [[Peter Watts (musician)|Overend Watts]], [[Verden Allen]] and the late [[Dale Griffin]] and Saxon members Graham Oliver and Steve Dawson amongst its management clients.\n\nSince 1997 the label has issued over 500 albums and 30 DVD titles. Its 500th release was the Stackridge live album ''The Final Bow'' two CD set.{{citation needed|date=April 2018}}\n\nOn 18 February 2019 the Purnells sold their shares in Angel Air Records and CeeDee Music UK to father and son team Brian and Terry Adams trading as The Store For Music Ltd. The Purnell's continue to own CeeDee Management Ltd who deal with music artist business affairs and royalty collections.\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of record labels]]\n\n==Further reading==\n*''Angel Air Is 10 (1997-2007)'' by James McCarraher; published by Sarum Publishing {{ISBN|978-0-9526690-2-9}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.angelair.co.uk/}}\n\n{{Normdaten}}\n[[Category:English record labels]]\n[[Category:British independent record labels]]\n[[Category:Pop record labels]]\n[[Category:Rock record labels]]\n[[Category:Record labels established in 1997]]\n[[Category:Reissue record labels]]\n[[Category:IFPI members]]\n\n\n{{UK-record-label-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2015}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2015}}\n{{Refimprove|date=September 2014}}\n{{Infobox record label <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Music -->\n| name        = Angel Air\n| image       = Angel_air_records_logo.gif\n| founded     = {{start date|1997}}\n| founder     = Peter Purnell, Shirley Purnell\n| distributor = Proper Music (UK)\n| genre       = Pop, rock, progressive rock, folk, world music, dance\n| country     = England\n| location    = Stowmarket, Suffolk\n| website      = {{URL|www.angelair.co.uk}}\n}}\n'''Angel Air''' is an English [[independent record label]] established in February 1997, specialising in reissues of classic [[pop music|pop]] and [[rock music|rock]] albums originally issued in the 1960s and 1970s (and latterly new albums from known artists up to the 21st century). It was formed by Peter and Shirley Purnell.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.angelair.co.uk/book_catalogue.htm |title=Angel Air Records - Classic Rock and Pop CD Albums - reissues, collectors items and new recordings |publisher=Angelair.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2013-03-02}}</ref> \n\nToday the Purnells also own CeeDee Music UK which publishes over 3,000 songs, and CeeDee Management which counts [[Mott The Hoople]] members the late [[Peter Watts (musician)|Overend Watts]], [[Verden Allen]] and the late [[Dale Griffin]] and Saxon members Graham Oliver and Steve Dawson amongst its management clients.\n\nSince 1997 the label has issued over 500 albums and 30 DVD titles. Its 500th release was the Stackridge live album ''The Final Bow'' two CD set.{{citation needed|date=April 2018}}\n\nOn 18 February 2019 the Purnells sold their shares in Angel Air Records and CeeDee Music UK to father and son team Brian and Terry Adams trading as The Store For Music Ltd. The Purnell\u2019s continue to own CeeDee Management Ltd who deal with music artist business affairs and royalty collections.\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of record labels]]\n\n==Further reading==\n*''Angel Air Is 10 (1997-2007)'' by James McCarraher; published by Sarum Publishing {{ISBN|978-0-9526690-2-9}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.angelair.co.uk/}}\n\n{{Normdaten}}\n[[Category:English record labels]]\n[[Category:British independent record labels]]\n[[Category:Pop record labels]]\n[[Category:Rock record labels]]\n[[Category:Record labels established in 1997]]\n[[Category:Reissue record labels]]\n[[Category:IFPI members]]\n\n\n{{UK-record-label-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: \u2019s \u2192 's", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Angel_Air_Records"}
